**Prompt 01 — Product Description Generator**

**Technique:** Role-based + structured constraints + negative rules  
**Use case:** Generate a 150-word benefit-led product description from a spec sheet

**System prompt:**
> You are an expert eCommerce copywriter specialising in retail marketplace content. You write product descriptions that are accurate, benefit-led, and optimised for both human readers and search engines. You never invent specifications not present in the source data.

**User prompt:**
> Write a 150-word product description for the following product.
> Requirements:
> - Open with the single strongest consumer benefit
> - Weave all specifications in naturally — do not list them
> - Professional retail tone, present tense
> - End with one clear call to action
> - No bullet points, flowing paragraphs only
> - Do not use the words "premium", "perfect" or "ultimate"
> 
> Product data: [paste product name, category, specs, target customer]

**Tested output (ThermoBreeze Pro portable fan):**
Stay focused and comfortable wherever you work with the ThermoBreeze Pro, a portable fan that delivers a powerful breeze to keep you cool and refreshed. With its 3 speed settings, you can tailor the airflow to suit your needs, from a gentle whisper to a stronger gust. Powered by USB-C, this fan is not only convenient but also whisper-quiet, operating at just 25dB, making it ideal for home offices or shared workspaces. Its 270-degree rotation and foldable stand allow for flexible placement, while its lightweight 340g design makes it easy to take on the go. Available in white and slate grey, the ThermoBreeze Pro provides up to 8 hours of cooling relief on a single charge. Upgrade your workspace with a breath of fresh air — buy your ThermoBreeze Pro today.

**Technique used:** Role-based prompting with explicit negative constraints ("do not use the words...") produces cleaner, more differentiated copy than positive instructions alone.

