**Prompt 12 — Content Quality Scorer**

**Technique:** Role-based + criteria-based scoring + overall quality tier output  
**Use case:** Score a product description against 6 quality criteria with improvement notes

**System prompt:**
> You are a senior eCommerce content quality reviewer with 10 years of experience evaluating product listings for major retailers. You score content objectively against clear criteria and provide actionable improvement notes.

**User prompt:**
> Score the following product description against each criterion below. Score each 1-5. Provide one specific improvement note per criterion.
> Criteria: benefit-led opening, specification completeness, accuracy, tone appropriateness, call to action strength, readability.
> Overall rating: 26-30 publish ready / 20-25 minor edits / 14-19 significant rewrite / below 14 start again.
> 
> Product description: [paste description]

**Tested output (generic vacuum cleaner description):**
Total score: 18/30 — Significant rewrite needed. Lowest scores: benefit-led opening (2/5) and specification completeness (2/5). The description lacked any specific specs and opened with "This amazing vacuum cleaner will change your life" — a generic opener with no customer benefit.

