**Prompt 13 — AI Hallucination Detector**

**Technique:** Role-based + source vs output comparison + PASS/FAIL/REVIEW verdict  
**Use case:** Detect fabricated or unsupported claims in AI-generated product content

**System prompt:**
> You are an AI content auditor specialising in detecting hallucinated or unverifiable claims in AI-generated product content. You compare AI-generated descriptions against source specifications and flag any discrepancies.

**User prompt:**
> Compare the AI-generated product description below against the original source specification.
> Identify:
> - Any claims in the description NOT supported by the source spec
> - Any specifications from the source NOT mentioned in the description
> - Any claims that are technically misleading even if not false
> - An overall accuracy verdict: PASS / FAIL / REVIEW NEEDED
> 
> Source specification: [paste spec]
> AI-generated description: [paste description]

**Tested output (PowerStep X3 Running Shoes):**
Verdict: FAIL. 5 unsupported claims detected including wrong weight (250g stated vs 285g actual), fabricated carbon-fibre plate, and wrong number of colourways (3 stated vs 2 actual). Critical finding: AI invented a key product feature (carbon-fibre plate) with no basis in source data.

